  "spec_link": "https://drafts.csswg.org/css-text-5/#text-fit-property",
  "api_spec": false,
  "automation_spec": false,
  "interop_compat_risks": "There is no compatibility risk because this is a new CSS property that affects nothing by default. \n\nRegarding accessibility, there is one open issue (https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/12886). While we may slightly adjust the behavior once a resolution is reached, the risk of breaking existing websites is very low. Therefore, we believe it is safe to ship the feature in its current state.",
  "all_platforms": true,
  "all_platforms_descr": null,
  "non_oss_deps": null,
  "anticipated_spec_changes": "There is one open issue regarding accessibility: https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/12886\n\nBecause this issue spans multiple working groups, reaching a resolution is expected to take a significant amount of time. Even when a solution is finalized, any potential specification changes would likely only result in minor adjustments (such as slight increases in font size). Therefore, we anticipate the compatibility risk to be minimal.\n",
